description: This area is weak. The listing of coursework is too generic. While relevant, it doesn't showcase specific projects or applications of these concepts. To improve, include specific projects or assignments where you applied these concepts and highlight any significant achievements or learnings. It's better to show, don't tell.

This area is weak. Describing the EvoGym project as 'A project from a tutorial video' diminishes its impact. While learning from tutorials is valuable, presenting it as a direct replication without any added innovation makes it less impressive. To improve, highlight any modifications, customizations, or enhancements you made beyond the tutorial's scope. This demonstrates initiative and problem-solving skills.

text: TikTok TechJam 2024 Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam
description: This area could be improved. Although it showcases experience, more technical details about this experience would be useful. Provide a summary of the challenge in the Hackathon and elaborate on the architecture of the solution developed. The number of team members and other important context would be more helpful.

The CV lacks any mention of testing or debugging skills. There's no indication of whether the candidate has experience writing unit tests, using debugging tools, or implementing testing strategies. Candidate can improve this by adding a section about this or mentioning projects that involve testing or debugging.
